This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to extract information from social media data. Specifically, it focuses on adverse drug reaction (ADR) extraction from tweets, which falls under the sub-category of clinical NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves multi-task learning and weak supervision techniques, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of large datasets, which is relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
